reviews.text:
Whether mornings, afternoons or evenings, it's a good place for a not-fancy get-together mall since it has a few restaurants which you can sit, eat and chat and no one will stare at you waiting for you to leave.

It's also a good place to walk around in cause it's got quite a few mobile carriers on the ground floor plus electronic shops on the 2nd floor.
A good variety of mobile phone peripherals, electronic gadgets, etc on sale.  A few cafes offer drinks and snacks if you get tired.
Good for electronics and great bag shop in 1st floor
Not as crowded as other shopping malls in Hong Kong. Easy shopping with some restaurants.
Pretty awesome discovery walking from Mong Kok to Prince Edward. Has shops from China mobile to most basic electronics, Remax and Starbucks with limited seats. if only a bit dated but with character.

reviews.text: 交通便利👍
環境雖然是很寬敞，但是座位編排得太過狹窄， 每上一個小菜都很急速，大部份小菜都是廉價，第一次去已令我失望！
服務 幾好 及菜式不過不失 但係比較 淺窄
價錢合理，員工細心有禮，本人参加社區中心活動時，貴分員工，時常替客人添热茶，热水，值得贊，关心長者。
坐電梯上落樓層很不方便，要等很久…
